Text.Value: Punch Astarion.
I understand you're upset, but let's not get carried away.
I need someone I can trust. Leave my party.
And I do apologise for last night. I may have gotten a little... overexcited?
Fine by me. So what would you like to talk about?
And of course, what happened last night shall never be repeated.
I don't want to talk about it.
How benevolent of you.
Thank goodness for that.
You betrayed my trust. I want you to leave.
Carried away? You killed me!
Oh, I feel much better now.
Agh! Gods damn it!

EditorData.AnimationTags: This one can use the Construction anim ThrowPunch and ReceivePunch
EditorData.NodeContext: Player punches you in the face

Text.Value: You looked a little ill last night, but you've certainly recovered.

EditorData.NodeContext: Stress on 'recovered' - the player's come back from the dead.

Text.Value: You can't be serious. You'd cast me out over this?
Do we? Why should I keep you around?
All right, but you can't drink people's blood from now on.
What do you say? Can we let bygones be bygones?
Anyway, last night was an aberration. It will never happen again.
Now, I admit, I got carried away last night. I apologise.
It had better not.
Cross my heart and hope to - you have my word.

EditorData.NodeContext: a tiny chuckle or something when he pauses before 'you have my word'

Text.Value: Fine, you can stay for as long as you're useful.
Fine. See how far you get without me.
'Killed' feels like a strong word. Not many corpses have your vigour.
Go. Now.
But look at you now - perfectly healthy! So let's not fall out over this. We still need each other, after all.
You can stay, but I need your word that this won't happen again.
No, I can't. I need you to leave.
Ill? You killed me!
Think of what you're losing. Now that I'm well-fed, I'm more capable than ever.
You're right, unfortunately. I can't lose any allies.
And the next time you get hungry? Who will you bite then?
Leave? You can't be serious.
Now, was there anything else?
That's the spirit! A team once again.
Fine, I forgive you.
A strong, well-fed vampire? I'm a powerful weapon - you'd be a fool to toss me aside now.

Synopsis:
Astarion killed you during the camp night where he bit you.
When you talk to him in the morning he tells you he was worried about you.
